  "customHelp": "Green = Harvester (gather energy). Red = Reaper (hunt). When you PLAY a Reaper or Harvester it enters your HOME zone. A creature can't push into TO INVADE (the opponent's area) until your NEXT turn (no invading the turn it's played). COUNTERS in order: Energy | Balance | Treachery. ENERGY = your spendable pool this turn (Raw + Life merged into one to cut clicks) — gain it at Dawn, spend it, convert leftover to Population at Dusk. BALANCE = your score. TREACHERY = how HARD YOUR LAND IS TO INVADE (1-10, STARTS AT 5). High = fortified; low = wide open, so you want YOURS high and your opponent's low. Greedy energy (e.g. Overdraw Rig) lowers your own treachery. ADAPTATIONS = your energy sites. You BUILD a 7-card ADAPTATION SIDE DECK in the deckbuilder, separate from your main deck (put them in the Sideboard). Pick ANY 7 from the Adaptation pool and MULTIPLE COPIES ARE ALLOWED — 4x Flux Field + 3x Overdraw Rig is a totally different deck from 3x Feed Vat + 4x Reclamation Site. At game start, park those 7 FACE DOWN in the ADAPTATION SIDE DECK pile on your board. At DAWN, flip the top one (revealed when played): SUN glyph = play it FREE right now; CRESCENT MOON glyph = take it to HAND and pay its cost to play it at DUSK. Played Adaptations sit in your SITES row — that's your energy base. POPULATION = red pips placed on your Harvesters (this is what accumulates). Play 1 Creator from your Creator Deck pile at start of turn. Tokens: red pip = Population, black = Death.",
